title: Led Zeppelin - 1980.06.21 Rotterdam, Netherlands
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1980.06.21 Rotterdam, Netherlands   

Artist: Led Zeppelin
Date: 1980-06-21 
Location: Rotterdam, Netherlands
Venue: Ahoyhallen
Source: Soundboard (90 minutes) with audience recordings to
fill in missing songs and gaps.

Soundboard Source: Incomplete excellent soundboard recording. 
Near 90 minutes. The recording is a very good balanced 
professional board tape.

Audience Source: Incomplete very good 1st audience recording. 
This is kinda clear recording. The tape is rather close to the 
stage but there are some audience noise near the recorder from 
time to time.

Tracklist:

01. Train Kept A Rollin' (AUD)
02. Nobody's Fault But Mine (AUD)
03. Black Dog (AUD)
04. In The Evening (AUD)
05. The Rain Song (SBD)
06. Hot Dog (SBD)
07. All Of My Love (SBD)
08. Trampled Underfoot (SBD)
09. Since I've Been Loving You (SBD)
10. Achilles Last Stand (SBD)
11. White Summer (SBD)
12. Kashmir (SBD)
13. Stairway To Heaven (SBD)
14. Rock And Roll (SBD)
15. Heartbreaker (SBD)

Comments: 
A truly excellent and fiery show in front of a dull and restrained 
crowd. The band is really playing well, and even Jimmy is on near 
top form, playing with guts, cleanly and constructing exciting solos 
and his usual great guitar playing. Trampled Underfoot is a definite 
highlight, and the encore of Heartbreaker is blistering
